Text.Value: A good ally - a good friend - would have weaned him off the mad hubris that tainted his otherwise brilliant mind.
There is one consolation - what remains of your soul is mine now, a new resident in my House of Hope.
Mystra obliterated him - erased him from existence as if he were an error in her ledger.
In time, long after you're gone, Gale Dekarios will cause such division and chaos in these Realms that even the lords of the Hells will be aghast to see it.
But I have assessed the situation, pondered every variable, plotted every possible course... and I have come to realise that this is for the best.
Do you really think that the Crown is safer in the hands of a goddess than in the claws of a devil?
A good person would have put a stop to his ambitions.
Your decimation did not even leave a mark on it. And now, only a fragment of your soul remains... and it is mine.

EditorData.logicalname: Avatar Gale became God and failed

Text.Value: My dear father Mephistopheles is among them.
The Crown really is marvelous - I'm almost tempted to dig Karsus' soul out of whatever pit he's in so I can show him what his creation is capable of now it's in the right hands.
Saving your world from the gods and monsters that threatened it wasn't enough.
The gods will be sundered. And from their ruin, I will rise.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade out on Raphael's terrible, satisfied smile.

Text.Value: Ta-ta for now.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade out on Raphael's terrible, satisfied smile.

Text.Value: It is thanks to you that Gale, the Wizard of Waterdeep, became Dekarios the Divine, god of ambition.
And I would have dealt fairly with you. I cannot say what Mystra will do.
You were the spark of ambition that rekindled Gale's ambitions, after Mystra had so cleverly put them to rest.

EditorData.logicalname: Gale tried to become God and failed

Text.Value: I will admit, I was angry when you failed to deliver the Crown to me. Those who break a deal with this devil do not usually live to tell the tale.
Even he sees how the tide has turned. And with all Nine Hells under my command, I will end The Blood War - inferna victoria - and look for new worlds to conquer.
Your life does not matter to me, but it wasn't the only thing lost. When you challenged Mystra, she took the Crown from you.
But mere survival was not enough. Not for Gale, and not for you.
There is one consolation - Gale's soul is mine now, a new resident in my House of Hope. Perhaps you'll come to visit one day.
You defied me, Wizard of Waterdeep, and you paid the price.

EditorData.logicalname: Avatar Gale became God and failed

Text.Value: I longed for the Crown, to satisfy my own ambitions, and I was furious that it had escaped me again.
In time, long after your friends and family are gone, you will cause such division and chaos in these Realms that even the lords of the Hells will be aghast to see it.

EditorData.logicalname: Gale Avatar became god of ambition

Text.Value: Obliterated by Mystra, you are but a fragment of what you were - all-but erased from existence as if you were an error in Mystra's ledger.
All is forgiven though. The Crown came to me, as promised, and the method of delivery was spectacular.
A thief, a liar, and a danger to anyone foolish enough to trust you.
Perhaps your soul will be part of my legions, Gale Dekarios. If enough of it remains when I'm done toying with it.

EditorData.logicalname: Avatar Gale became God and failed

Text.Value: And you are the reason he survived the appetites of the tadole for so long.
You, by word and by deed, encouraged him to indulge his worst impulses, and now he is gone.
It is the gods who almost brought doom to your world. I was merely a witness to their conspiracy.
Spurred on by your victory over the Netherbrain, he took it upon himself to challenge Mystra for control of her domain.
You harnessed its power, as Karsus once did, and you too fell into ruin. You were halfway to heaven when the orb detonated, tearing you apart.

EditorData.logicalname: Avatar Gale became God and failed

Text.Value: We had an agreement, and you broke it. The Crown was supposed to be mine.
My legions are beginning their assault on Zariel's Flying Fortress just about now - it will fall before the sun rises over Toril, and Avernus will be mine.
Instead of delivering it to its true home in the Hells, you allowed Gale Dekarios to deliver it to Mystra.
We're going to have such fun together.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade out on Raphael's terrible, satisfied smile.

Text.Value: It would have feasted on that impressive mind of his, and all of his talent would have been snuffed out forever.
The tadpole would have feasted on that impressive mind of yours if you hadn't fought so hard.

EditorData.logicalname: Gale Avatar became god of ambition

Text.Value: When that is done, I will need new worlds to conquer.
You were the spark that rekindled Gale's hubris, and set him on a course that will make Celestia quake.
Look to the history of these Realms. It is not the devils but the gods who sunder, wreck and ruin - it is the gods who instigate each new crisis.
Spurred on by your victory over the Netherbrain, you took it upon yourself to challenge Mystra for control of her domain.
Ta-ta for now.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade out on Raphael's terrible, satisfied smile.

Text.Value: You.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade in: Raphael in a void, addressing the camera as if speaking directly to the player.

Text.Value: Conquering the other Hells will be simplicity itself - some of the Archdevils are already making overtures of peace and promises of tribute.
Gale harnessed its power, as Karsus once did, and he too fell into ruin. He was halfway to heaven when the orb detonated, tearing him apart.
Ambition. Such a delicious sin for mortalkind to indulge in - such a dreadful weapon for an immortal to wield.
He thought it would give him an advantage, that it would protect him from the fury of a god. He was wrong.
It won't be long before I come knocking at your door.
I will bend the Crown to my will now, and use its power to bring the Nine Hells under my command
All that remained were ashes, blood, tears... and the Crown. Always the Crown.
Instead of delivering it to its true home in the Hells, you gifted it to Mystra.
A thief, a liar, and a fool.
It won't be long before I come knocking at your door.
You.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade in: Raphael in a void, addressing the camera as if speaking directly to the player.

Text.Value: I owe you thanks.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade in: Raphael in a void, addressing the camera as if speaking directly to the player.

Text.Value: Your mad hubris tainted your otherwise brilliant mind.
Perhaps the crown is a mere trinket to one of her power, or perhaps it is the key to unlocking some dreadful new potential in her portfolio.
Gale wanted more, and you encouraged him to ignore every sensible instinct, to ignore the lesson of Karsus' Folly, and to reach for the heavens.
I owe you a debt of gratitude.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade in: Raphael in a void, addressing the camera as if speaking directly to the player.

Text.Value: When Mystra eliminated Gale, the Crown was lost too. Either destroyed, or claimed by the goddess and hidden away where I cannot sense its presence.
Ambition. Courage. Hope. They all burn you in the end.
But mere survival was not enough for you.

EditorData.logicalname: Gale Avatar became god of ambition

Text.Value: Time will tell, as it always does. Look to the heavens and pray for peace - but  prepare for a cataclysm.
His life does not matter to me, but Gale wasn't the only thing lost. When he challenged Mystra, he took the Crown with him.
Without you, he would not have survived the appetites of the tadpole.
My door is always open to old friends.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Fade out on Raphael's terrible, satisfied smile.

Text.Value: The decimation of Gale did not even leave a mark on it.
You wanted more, and the mad hubris that has always tainted you came to the fore. Now that the Crown is yours, you will make Celestia quake.

EditorData.logicalname: Gale Avatar became god of ambition

Text.Value: Now it is out of my grasp once more. Either destroyed, or claimed by the goddess and hidden away where I cannot sense its presence.
Gale Dekarios trusted you. And do you know what became of him?
I should snuff you out and make coin of your soul, but it will be more amusing to let you see the consequences of your actions.

Synopsis: After WithersChronicles, if the player made the deal with Raphael (the Orphic Hammer in exchange for the Crown of Karsus), Raphael shows up to report back on how that went.
